Fire has razed the residence of Osun governorship candidate of Accord party, Dr Akin Ogunbiyi ahead of Saturday poll. It was gathered the fire started at the private room of Ogunbiyi at Ile-Ogbo in Ayedire Local Government area around 7:45pm on Sunday before it was extinguished. A statement by the Ogunbiyi’s campaign team, Bishop Seun Adeoye, confirmed the incident but refused to disclosed the cause of the fire.   Ganduje frees 90 inmates in celebration of Sallah     Nigeria under siege of terrorists, bandits – ACF      Nigeria faring better under Buhari – Presidency   “Ogunbiyi thanked the people of the state for sympathising with him over the fire incidence which occurred in his private residence on Sunday,” he stated. He declared he cherished the concerns and prayers of his teaming supporters over the incident. Ogunbiyi stated that whatever happens, he was determined to liberate the people of this State from bad and wicked governance at all levels. The Accord candidate advised the people to vote for him with their conscience for a new dawn in the State.